{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5fb0fc1e-43d9-4a1b-b9e3-ff7e171f5ea0","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_oSfdkPXZYP4epJSUNqvOyC","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Answering MSTest SDK question"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_vIIimPNZlihtK2H1j5Pxoe","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9fc7a30eb6fb49c89a29f6084721cad6"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-9fc7a30eb6fb49c89a29f6084721cad6."}],"interactionId":"d1ef6e57-9ed4-4a02-a682-23785d8dd6bb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically around test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes - let me look at what's in the working directory first to see if there's relevant context, but this is likely something I can answer from knowledge.\n\nThe key change is that starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8 or around version 3.x/4.x, MSTest moved to Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default runner instead of VSTest. In MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the VSTest compatibility layer was removed by default, meaning `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run tests unless you explicitly opt back in.\n\n\nTo restore the old behavior, you can set `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` in your project file to re-enable the VSTest adapter, or you can migrate to using `dotnet test` with the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner instead of calling vstest.console directly.","outputTokens":463,"requestId":"BD17:23AB21:213CB51:257ED1F:6A07D61A"},"id":"1c334b2b-f7e6-4b2d-9a86-3faaef52127d","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:27:49.282Z","parentId":"98fa37a8-3e31-4629-9b24-323b1a9cc613"}
