{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9aacb811-d13f-4cd3-828a-8a26cacedbe7","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0+ removed the VSTest compatibility layer by default.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK included the VSTest adapter bridge so `vstest.console` could still discover and run tests. Starting with 4.0, only Microsoft.Testing.Platform is shipped — `vstest.console` no longer works out of the box.\n\n**You have two options:**\n\n1. **Opt back into VSTest** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n2. **Migrate your CI to the new runner** (recommended) — replace `vstest.console` with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test --no-build\n   ```\n   or run the test executable directly. The new platform supports `--list-tests`, `--filter`, TRX loggers, etc.\n\nOption 2 is the intended path forward — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is faster and doesn't require the VSTest translation layer.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d1ef6e57-9ed4-4a02-a682-23785d8dd6bb","outputTokens":245,"requestId":"BD0A:1A8D4E:1FB4951:23FAE75:6A07D624"},"id":"854f18cc-4bf3-4d38-93d7-7afd5a1f07bc","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:27:55.517Z","parentId":"d0a7732e-4d4a-4119-871d-b9063883ff25"}
